The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for somatic variant calling in cancer, which is a problem in bioinformatics. The paper specifically focuses on the use of Bayesian neural networks, which are a type of machine learning algorithm commonly used in computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI, and q-bio.GN (Genomics), as the paper deals with genomic data. q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods) is also a possibility, as the paper discusses the use of probability estimates for variant calling. Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely possibility, as the paper deals with image data (sequencing data), but the focus is on machine learning rather than computer vision specifically.
